text: Anitra is an Arabic-sounding female given name, originally invented in the 1860s by the playwright Henrik Ibsen for a minor character in his play Peer Gynt. It later became popular as a female name in Scandinavian countries. Notable people with the name include: *Anitra Ahtola *Anitra Ford *Anitra Rasmussen *Anitra Steen == See also == *1016 Anitra, a main-belt asteroid *Anitra's Dance Category:Feminine given names
